    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-07-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-07-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="999"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d999">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Germany)/7–3045:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 999<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_KGF1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Kennan</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d999fn1">Printed from the text received in the
                        Department of State.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Babelsberg</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-07-30">July 30,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Victory1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Victory</hi>
                    </gloss> 419. Sent to Moscow repeated Department for information.</p>
                <p>Re note delivered to Soviets on German assets in Spain,<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d999fn2">See <ref target="#d997">document No. 997</ref>.</note> we
                    have received word from US Military Attaché, Stockholm,<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d999fn3">
                        <persName corresp="#p_KBGAAJ1">Brigadier General Alfred A. Kessler,
                            Jr.</persName>
                    </note> that Russian Delegation has conducted a survey in Sweden of interned
                    German planes (presumably including only those coming to Sweden from
                    Soviet-German front), which are proposed to be flown out as <gloss
                        target="#t_War1">war</gloss> booty.<note n="4" xml:id="d999fn4">See <ref
                            target="#d990">document No. 990</ref>.</note> Newspapers have publicized
                    Russian plans, together with statement that no request concerning remainder has
                    been made by US or <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_OCT1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
